RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea anemone
<hw>Sea" a*nem"o*ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one
of numerous species of soft-bodied Anthozoa, belonging to the order
<ord>Actinaria</ord>; an actinian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They have the oral disk surrounded by one or more
circles of simple tapering tentacles, which are often very numerous, and
when expanded somewhat resemble the petals of flowers, with colors
varied and often very beautiful.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea ape</ent>⟦br⟧
